FBIS3-26176 "drchi023_a_94006" FBIS-CHI-94-023 Document Type:Daily Report 3 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing Welcomes Improved U.S.-SRV Ties OW0302092994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0923 GMT 3 Feb 94 OW0302092994 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, February 3 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese Government welcomes the decision of the United States to lift the trade embargo on Vietnam since the improvement of U.S.-Vietnamese ties will benefit the stability and prosperity of the Asia-Pacific region. Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Wu Jianmin said this at a weekly press conference here this afternoon while commenting on recent reports that the United States will lift the embargo very soon. The embargo was imposed about two decades ago. Wu also said that Sino-Vietnamese relations in various fields are developing smoothly.
